latestPosts.caption:
Hello everyone! This is Bishal @visualsoptimist, a digital artist based in Northeast India. Today, in this #MadeWithPhotoshop tutorial, I'll show you how I created this moody composition. 

To start with, I placed an image of the mountains of Dzukou Valley, Nagaland, that I wanted to keep in the farthest distance and masked the sky with the quick selection tool. 

I then experimented by placing two layers of different skies in the background of the first image. It looked decent so I continued with it. 

I then placed another image of Dzukou Valley above the first image and masked the sky. 

I then duplicated the layer a few times to distribute it over the canvas so that the mountains look evenly distributed. 

Then, to establish distance between the background and the foreground, I added an image of abandoned cottages in a mountain and cut and pasted the dwellings in the vacant spaces. 

Then I added images of two trees, masked them using Channels, copied and pasted it to both sides of the foreground to complement the foreground. 

In the following steps, I put more grass above the foreground, a chimney behind the main cottage, and a small human subject. 

I then used a Hue & Saturation adjustment layer to add windows to the cottages and some fogs and glows to the composition to enhance ambience. 

Then I added highlights to the composition and a sun behind the mountains. 

I then experimented by including little flying birds, fences behind the cottages, and other elements to enhance the composition. 

Finally, I used the Camera Raw Filter to color grade the image and give a moody feel to it. I hope you enjoy the tutorial. If you like it, don't forget to check my profile for such compositions. 

All stock images used were downloaded from Unsplash. 

Thank You! I hope you have a wonderful day. 
. 
.

latestPosts.caption:
Once upon a time, there was a magical forest located deep inside the highest mountains. It was home to many unique and mystical creatures, including three bears named Baloo, Koda, and Yogi.
The forest was abundant in various herbs and plants that possessed incredible healing powers. The locals would come to the forest to gather these herbs, which were used to cure diseases and ailments that the outside world had no cure for.
One day, an evil sorcerer learned about the magical forest and its healing powers. He planned to destroy the forest and take control of the herbs for his own selfish purposes. The locals of the forest were terrified, and they knew they had to protect the forest at all costs.
That's when the three bears stepped in. Baloo, Koda, and Yogi were known for their bravery and strength, and they volunteered to guard the forest and protect its people and plants from the sorcerer's evil plans.
The bears had the ability to communicate with the plants and animals of the forest, and they worked tirelessly to keep the sorcerer and his army at bay. They fought fiercely, but the sorcerer's power was too great.
In a last-ditch effort to save the forest, Baloo, Koda, and Yogi pooled their magical powers and created a shield around the forest that would protect it from harm. The shield was so powerful that the sorcerer and his army couldn't break through.
The forest was saved, and the locals could continue to gather the herbs that they needed to save lives and heal the sick. The three bears became legendary heroes in the forest, and their legacy lived on for generations.
.
.
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
The hybrid - Here's my entry for #editwartransformations for @benny_productions Spooky Edit War 2022

The hybrid character I created here is known as a centaur, a creature from greek mythology with the upper body (torso) of a human being, and the lower body and legs of a horse. 

They would reside near forests and mountains because those areas are ideal for their survival and their physical needs. According to legend, they lived in tribes, made their dwellings in caverns, and defended themselves by using boulders and tree branches.

A centaur with unusually evil magical abilities seemed like a nice match for Benny this Spooktober.

In this composition, 95% of the character's body is painted as I was unable to get the desired form in the stocks available. 
Hope you all enjoy this edit.
Thank you!
.
.

The Aftermath _

It is all so quiet now. Too quiet. Even though I grew up around here, after civilization lost it’s way and nature took over, it feels like this town is a whole other place. With everything gone, just a blanket of greenery and moss remains. This place has changed because it was time for nature to reclaim.
.
